+    <h2>Gravity-Powered Car (Recycled Materials)</h2>
+
+    <section class="project-media">
+      <figure><img src="../images/sketch1.jpg" alt="Sketches of gravity car (top/side)"><figcaption>Sketch 1 — concept views (top/side/bottom)</figcaption></figure>
+      <figure><img src="../images/sketch2.jpg" alt="Sketch showing ballast cavity"><figcaption>Sketch 2 — added cavity for ballast weight</figcaption></figure>
+    </section>
+
+    <section class="project-explanation">
+      <h3>Design notes</h3>
+      <ul>
+        <li>Body: lightweight styrofoam or recycled plastic shaped for low drag.</li>
+        <li>Wheels: low friction bearings and aligned axles; holes placed as in sketches.</li>
+        <li>Ballast: added metal block in a cavity (see sketch 2) to tune mass distribution for downhill runs.</li>
+        <li>Testing: adjust axle alignment and wheel symmetry to minimize frictional losses.</li>
+      </ul>
+    </section>
+
+    <a class="btn" href="../projects.html">Back to projects</a>
