+    <h2>Flight Path Simulation (Python)</h2>
+
+    <section class="project-media">
+      <figure><img src="../images/project2.svg" alt="Flight sim illustration"><figcaption>Simulation concept and sample output visuals</figcaption></figure>
+      <figure><img src="../images/fuelplot.png" alt="Fuel flow plot"><figcaption>Fuel Flow Plot — fuel flow vs altitude under varying winds</figcaption></figure>
+      <figure><img src="../images/fuelplot2.png" alt="Additional fuel flow variant"><figcaption>Additional fuel flow plot (user-supplied image)</figcaption></figure>
+    </section>
+
+    <section class="project-explanation">
+      <h3>Simulation details</h3>
+      <p>The simulation models a simplified point-mass aircraft system with basic aerodynamic assumptions and a thrust model. Numerical integration is performed with a fixed-step RK4 integrator. Plots show how wind conditions (headwind/tailwind/no wind) affect fuel flow across altitudes.</p>
+
+      <h4>Source & how to run</h4>
+      <p>See the repo for the Python scripts. Run: <code>python3 simulate.py</code> (requirements: numpy, matplotlib). Output images are generated to the plots/ directory.</p>
+    </section>
+
+    <a class="btn" href="../projects.html">Back to projects</a>
+  </main>
